<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--GrannyGrenade     07-09 0118</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Granny Grenade,0121</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman Cleans Out Attic, Dumps Grenade</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LA SPEZIA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An elderly woman tossed a hand grenade
into a garbage dump and announced, ``Enough already, I can't keep
this in the attic any more,'' authorities said.
   Police blocked off the area after learning of the incident and
eventually fished out the American-made grenade, whose pin had not
been removed.
   No one was injured in the incident Friday in La Spezia, 200
miles north of Rome.
   After the woman disposed of the grenade, she told bystanders,
``I have thrown it away and now it's up to you,'' the Italian news
agency ANSA said.
   The woman left the area and was not found, police said.
</TEXT>
