<HEAD>Names In The News</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY14</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dudley Moore says his sensitivity to alcohol
abuse tempered his portrayal of the lovable lush ``Arthur'' in the
sequel ``Arthur 2 On The Rocks.''
   Moore, who won an Oscar nomination for his performance as the
drunken millionaire Arthur Bach, said his approach to the character
this time was different because of a heightened awareness of
alcoholism.
   ``There was no official pressure from the studio or from any
organized groups,'' Moore said recently. ``But I personally have an
educated awareness of the problem.''
   The producers also avoided any scenes in ``Arthur 2 On The
Rocks'' of Arthur drinking and driving, unlike the original, in
which Arthur is seen cruising in his Rolls Royce swigging from a
bottle.
   ``There's a scene in which Linda (Liza Minnelli) says she never
lets him drink and drive,'' Moore said. ``And you can tell that
Arthur knows exactly what he should or should not do. He still gets
very drunk, but that's because he feels panicked and isolated
sometimes and unable to cope with the world.''
   But Moore is quick to point out that the film doesn't preach.
   The sequel opened Friday at theaters nationwide.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Duchess of York, who is eight months pregnant,
escaped injury when her chauffeured car collided with an oncoming
vehicle, police and Buckingham Palace said.
   The accident occurred Friday on a section of the M40, a busy
highway about 20 miles outside of London. Part of the road was
closed for repairs, police said.
   A police bodyguard was driving the duchess' Jaguar. She
continued the journey in an accompanying police car, Buckingham
Palace said.
   The 28-year-old duchess, the former Sarah Ferguson, is married
to Prince Andrew, the second son of Queen Elizabeth II. She is
expecting their first child.
</TEXT>
