<TEXT>
   Veteran actor Carlos Riquelme, who stars in
Robert Redford's ``The Milagro Beanfield War,'' was reported in
serious condition at a local hospital's coronary care unit.
   But the 77-year-old actor ``has been improving in the past
hours,'' said Rodolfo Ocampo, a doctor the Hospital Santelena.
   Riquelme's brother Victor told the newspaper El Universal the
stress of filming of the movie in New Mexico last year may have
contributed to his illness.
   ``The pace ... was exhausting. He was working nearly 14 hours a
day,'' Victor Riquelme said.
