<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Ramones, the band that gave the world
``Cretin Hop,'' ``Teen-age Lobotomy'' and other short, loud, fast
and somewhat silly punk tunes, is celebrating its 15th anniversary.
   The Ramones _ Joey, Johnny, Dee Dee, and Marky Ramone, who are
not related but took the surname for the stage _ marked the
milestone recently by releasing ``Ramonesmania,'' a two-record
anthology of their best-known material.
   Except for an occasional guitar solo by Johnny Ramone _ a lapse
some fans equate with selling out _ the anthology shows the punk
pioneers have stuck to the formula of two-minute, three-cord
head-bangers.
   ``We're a band that our fans can count on,'' Joey Ramone said
recently.
