<TEXT>
   Former President Richard M. Nixon is
recuperating from a short hospital stay for hernia surgery, a
spokeswoman said.
   ``It was a procedure called the Canadian repair, a very commonly
performed surgical procedure and it was performed under local
anesthesia,'' said Myrna Manners, spokeswoman at New York
Hospital-Cornell Medical Center.
   Nixon, 75, was admitted Wednesday and was operated on Thursday
morning by George Wantz, a hernia expert. He was discharged Friday.
   He is to recuperate at his home in Saddle River, N.J., Manners
said.
   ``It was really very routine, very minor surgery. And he went
home in good condition,'' she said.
