<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments Friday from the
presidential campaign trail:
   
   GEORGE BUSH, saying the timing his appearance at a GOP
fundraiser in Atlanta isn't aimed at the Democrats: ``We are not
going to rain on their parade. That is not to say we're not praying
for rain.''
   
   PAUL KIRK, Democratic party chairman, suggesting Bush may have
violated the law by using tax money for campaign trips: ``The only
thing that matches the hypocrisy of the Republican Party of the
1980s claiming to be the party of fiscal conservatism is the
Republican Party of the 1980s preaching about law and order.''
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, appearing in Texarkana with Texas Sen. Lloyd
Bentsen, asked whether Bentsen might be more valuable remaining in
the Senate than joining him on the Democratic ticket: ``I'm
pondering. He could make a great contribution in this county in
many, many ways. He already has.''
   
   JESSE JACKSON, on Bush's recent pledge to appoint a Hispanic to
his Cabinet if elected president: ``Bush came through here the
other day talking about his conversion to a new religion _
respecting Hispanics is a new religion of his.''
