<HEAD>Search For Missing Ship Called Off</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CANBERRA, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rescuers today called off their
search for a cargo ship carrying 26 Filipino seamen that had been
missing for six days, authorities said.
   The Singa Sea lost radio contact on Sunday during rough weather
about 1,200 nautical miles off the coast of Western Australian
state, said Leone Jorgensen, spokeswoman for the Coastal
Surveillance Authority.
   Aircraft have found no sign of the vessel, she said.
