<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Burma     07-09 0147</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Burma,0151</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Authorities Lift Curfew Imposed After Riots</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RANGOON, Burma (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities today lifted a dusk-to-dawn
curfew that was imposed in Rangoon after thousands of students
rioted in the streets on June 21, state radio said.
   A ban on public gatherings also was lifted, the broadcast said.
   According to the government, six policemen and three civilians
were killed in the rioting. The violence erupted after university
students pressed demands, including release of colleagues detained
in earlier protests, and the government responded by closing the
schools.
   The government said that on Thursday and Friday, it freed all
784 people detained in connection with last month's riots and other
rioting in March. Of those, 288 were students, it said.
   The government also for the first time made a concession to
student demands, announcing on Friday that students expelled from
schools for the March-June demonstrations will be readmitted.
</TEXT>
