<HEAD>Ferry And Ship Collide In The Strait of Messina</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Italian ferry and a Panamanian container ship
collided in the Strait of Messina on Saturday, injuring at least
three people, the Italian news agency ANSA said.
   Three passengers on the ferry La Edra, which runs between
Messina, Sicily, and Reggio Calabria on the mainland, were taken to
a hospital for X-rays, the agency said. It said an unspecified
number of others suffered bruises and contusions.
   The agency said port officials were investigating the accident,
which occurred 1.7 miles off the point of San Raineri. The ferry
suffered damage to the bow, and the container ship Langueloc was
damaged near the middle of its right side, ANSA said.
