<1ST_LINE>u i AM-Train-TruckCrash 2ndLd-Writethru   07-09 0177</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Train-Truck Crash, 2nd Ld-Writethru,a0623,0179</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Train Hits Flatbed Truck Filled With Passengers; At Least 16
Killed</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES with death toll rising to 16</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BUENOS AIRES, Argentina (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A train collided with a truck
loaded with opposition party activists going to vote Saturday, and
at least 16 people were killed and 11 seriously injured, officials
said.
   The accident took place at El Quebrachal, a small town 150 miles
southeast of the provincial capital of Salta. The town's mayor,
Pedro Sandez, said the crash occurred when a flatbed truck collided
with a train at an unmarked rail crossing.
   Thirty people were in the truck, including several children.
Most were opposition Peronist Party activists headed to vote in
primary elections to choose their party's presidential candidate.
   Seven of the injured were taken to a hospital in grave condition
in the nearby town of Joaquin V. Gonzalez, officials said.
   No further details were immediately available.
   The presidential election will be held next year. Last week,
Eduardo Angeloz was chosen the candidate of the governing Radical
Civic Union Party.
